# meta-repo-build-root-pattern — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-03-29)

**Changed by:** Odysseus full e2e build session — all 5 targets passing
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Updated Mojo delegation pattern: use `BUILD_ROOT="{{BUILD_ROOT}}/<Name>" just build` env var override instead of delegating without any build dir control
- ProjectOdyssey adopts `env_var_or_default("BUILD_ROOT", ...)` so it works from both its own dir and the meta-repo
- When Podman is running and BUILD_ROOT is outside the workspace, `_run` mounts it at `/ext-build` and rewrites paths — no `NATIVE=1` needed
- Added `_test-keystone` to complete the test recipe (Keystone was missing)
- Added link to related skill `cpp-scaffold-cmake-test-path-fix`
- Updated Results & Parameters to reflect full end-to-end build (all 5 targets verified)
- Added history frontmatter field

### Why
PR #67 added the build recipes, but the initial implementation had two gaps discovered during
the first full e2e build run (PR #68):
1. `_build-odyssey` had no way to redirect Mojo build artifacts — needed BUILD_ROOT env var
   pattern in ProjectOdyssey's justfile so artifacts land in root build/ProjectOdyssey/
2. `test` recipe only covered 3 of 4 C++ repos (Keystone was missing)

---

## v1.0.0 (2026-03-29)

**Initial version.** Documented BUILD_ROOT pattern as part of PR #67.
